{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:28:05.760648+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Summary\n\n### NPM Scripts for Local Development & Deployment\n\nThis repository is a **Create React App template** (`cra-template-firebase-starter`). There are two sets of scripts:\n\n#### 1. Root `package.json` – scripts for the *template maintainer* (publishing the template itself)\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `start` | `react-scripts start` | Start the development server |\n| `build` | `react-scripts build` | Create a production build |\n| `test` | `react-scripts test` | Run the test suite |\n| `eject` | `react-scripts eject` | Eject from CRA |\n| `predeploy` | `npm run build` | Automatically build before deploying |\n| `deploy` | `gh-pages -d build` | Deploy the `build/` folder to GitHub Pages |\n| `clean-files` | `rm -rf ./template/public ./template/src` | Clean template directories before repackaging |\n| `copy-files` | `cp -a ./src/. template/src && cp -a ./public/. template/public` | Copy current source into the template dirs |\n| `prepublishOnly` | `npm run clean-files && npm run copy-files` | Runs automatically before `npm publish` |\n\n#### 2. `template.json` – scripts that *end users* get in their generated project\n\nIn addition to `start`, `build`, `test`, `eject`, `predeploy`, and `deploy` (same as above), users also get:\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `serve` | `serve -s build` | Serve the production build locally (single-page app mode) |\n| `build-and-serve` | `npm run build && npm run serve` | Build the production bundle and serve it locally in one step |\n| `pull` | `git pull && npm i && npm start` | Pull latest, install dependencies, and start dev server |\n\n---\n\n### Repository Guidance for Testing a Production Build Locally\n\nFrom the **README** (under \"To Deploy on GitHub Pages\", step 3):\n\n> **\"Test production build locally\"** (optional):\n>\n> 1. **Update** the `homepage` field in `package.json` to `\"/\"`.\n> 2. **Install** `serve` globally:\n>    ```bash\n>    npm i -g serve\n>    ```\n> 3. **Run** the combined build-and-serve script:\n>    ```bash\n>    npm run build-and-serve\n>    ```\n\nThis workflow:\n1. Sets the homepage to `/` so that asset paths resolve correctly when served from a local server (rather than a GitHub Pages subdirectory).\n2. Uses the `serve` package (a static file server) to host the production build.\n3. The `build-and-serve` script (defined in `template.json`) first runs `react-scripts build` to produce an optimized production bundle in `build/`, then immediately serves it via `serve -s build` (the `-s` flag enables SPA mode, redirecting all unknown paths to `index.html` for client-side routing).\n\nThis lets you verify the production build behaves correctly (routing, authentication redirects, asset loading) *before* pushing to GitHub Pages or publishing.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1381, "prompt_tokens": 9353, "total_tokens": 10734, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 666, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8832}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 8832, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 521}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "9fb71f88-632a-4bba-a832-e2d5756db24a", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea57c-955d-7e53-9ba4-cb6ea64b32dd-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9353, "output_tokens": 1381, "total_tokens": 10734, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 8832}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 666}}}}]}}}
